item.title: Project 1: Health Across the States
item.description: Introduction This project centers around American health. I first chose two datasets from the CDC's BRFSS Prevalence & Trends Data, both from 2019. One of these data sets contained information regarding weight using the metric of BMI, specifically examining the percentage of the population in each BMI category by state. The original data included 28 columns, and most of these were formatting for the CDC's system of display. The variables I used from this data set included state, percentage underweight, percentage normal weight, percentage overweight, and percentage obese.
